<span style="color:rgb(28, 30, 33)">Rockingham County Public Schools has established a new "RCPS Innovation Update" page. It contains a link to a letter that Superintendent Dr. Oskar Scheikl sent out to all parents from all six schools in the TAHS attendance area on March 3 concerning the shortened day pilot that will begin in August of 2020. It also contains links to a new input form that may be used by parents, community members, teachers and staff, and students. A new FAQ document is provided, as well as </span><span style="color:rgb(28, 30, 33)">a link to the previous page with all of the presentations from November 2019 through February 2020.<br>Link to the new page: <a href="https://www.smore.com/4jsb2?fbclid=IwAR0JEf4g5bi1cFKm4EKLGRKQNphNjYTul_iDtCkq0tjnCSdxMd0UJ-vald0" target="_blank">https://www.smore.com/4jsb2</a><br>This RCPS Innovation Update page will be used regularly to communicate with parents and the RCPS community about not only the shortened day pilot in the TA area but also about work that is going on with curriculum and other important topics of interest.</span>
